g.text: UML Diagram: Class SubstantiveConceptualDomain in Context
- Move the mouse cursor over a name to see more information.
- Click on a name to go to the corresponding page.
- The arrows of the inheritance tree are

a.title: ― ConceptualVariable: A variable at the highest level of abstraction.
a.xlink:title: ― ConceptualVariable: A variable at the highest level of abstraction.

a.title: ― SubstantiveValueDomain: Value domain for a substantive conceptual domain. Typically a description and/or enumeration of allowed values of interest.
a.xlink:title: ― SubstantiveValueDomain: Value domain for a substantive conceptual domain. Typically a description and/or enumeration of allowed values of interest.

a.title: ― ConceptualDomain: Set of concepts, where each concept is intended to be used as the meaning (signified) for a datum.
a.xlink:title: ― ConceptualDomain: Set of concepts, where each concept is intended to be used as the meaning (signified) for a datum.

a.title: ― CatalogDetails: A set of information useful for attribution, data discovery, and access.
a.xlink:title: ― CatalogDetails: A set of information useful for attribution, data discovery, and access.

a.title: ― LabelForDisplay: A structured display label. Label provides display content of a fully human readable display for the identification of the object.
a.xlink:title: ― LabelForDisplay: A structured display label. Label provides display content of a fully human readable display for the identification of the object.

a.title: ― Identifier: Identifier for objects requiring short- or long-lasting referencing and management.
a.xlink:title: ― Identifier: Identifier for objects requiring short- or long-lasting referencing and management.

a.title: ― ConceptualValue: Concept (with a notion of equality defined) being observed, captured, or derived which is associated to a single data instance.
a.xlink:title: ― ConceptualValue: Concept (with a notion of equality defined) being observed, captured, or derived which is associated to a single data instance.

a.title: ― ValueAndConceptDescription: Formal description of a set of values.
a.xlink:title: ― ValueAndConceptDescription: Formal description of a set of values.

a.title: ― ConceptSystem: Set of concepts structured by the relations among them [GSIM 1.1].
a.xlink:title: ― ConceptSystem: Set of concepts structured by the relations among them [GSIM 1.1].

a.title: ― takesSubstantiveConceptsFrom: Identifies the substantive conceptual domain containing the set of substantive concepts used to describe the conceptual variable.
a.xlink:title: ― takesSubstantiveConceptsFrom: Identifies the substantive conceptual domain containing the set of substantive concepts used to describe the conceptual variable.

a.title: ― takesConceptsFrom: Corresponding conceptual definition given by an substantive conceptual domain.
a.xlink:title: ― takesConceptsFrom: Corresponding conceptual definition given by an substantive conceptual domain.

a.title: ― isDescribedBy: A description of the concepts in the domain. A numeric domain might use a logical expression to be machine actionable; a text domain might use a regular expression to describe strings that describe the concepts.
a.xlink:title: ― isDescribedBy: A description of the concepts in the domain. A numeric domain might use a logical expression to be machine actionable; a text domain might use a regular expression to describe strings that describe the concepts.

a.title: ― takesConceptsFrom: Conceptual domain takes concept from zero to one concept system.
a.xlink:title: ― takesConceptsFrom: Conceptual domain takes concept from zero to one concept system.

a.title: ― hasConceptFrom: Conceptual value has concept from one conceptual domain.
a.xlink:title: ― hasConceptFrom: Conceptual value has concept from one conceptual domain.
